---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="ABC Notation 101 · Old Toby Academy"
  description="The fundamentals of ABC notation — letters and ledger lines, dynamics, timing — with a live editor, audio playback, and a 15-question quiz."
  activeNav="courses"
  footerVariant="short"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <!-- abcjs for staff rendering & playback -->
    <script is:inline src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/abcjs@6.4.4/dist/abcjs-basic-min.js"></script>
  </Fragment>

  <div slot="body-top" class="progress-rail"><div class="progress-fill" id="progressFill"></div></div>

  <main class="page">
    <div class="crumbs">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span>›</span>
      <a href="/courses">Courses</a><span>›</span>
      <em>ABC Notation 101</em>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-layout">

      <!-- ============ TOC SIDEBAR ============ -->
      <aside class="sidebar-toc">
        <div class="eyebrow">In this lesson</div>
        <ul class="toc-list">
          <li><a href="#intro" class="active"><span class="num">i</span>Introduction</a></li>
          <li><a href="#features"><span class="num">ii</span>Key features</a></li>
          <li><a href="#headers"><span class="num">iii</span>Header syntax</a></li>
          <li><a href="#notes"><span class="num">iv</span>Note syntax</a></li>
          <li><a href="#dynamics"><span class="num">v</span>Dynamics</a></li>
          <li><a href="#timing"><span class="num">vi</span>Timing</a></li>
          <li><a href="#playground"><span class="num">vii</span>Playground</a></li>
          <li><a href="#exercise"><span class="num">viii</span>Exercise</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quiz"><span class="num">ix</span>Quiz</a></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <!-- ============ READER ============ -->
      <article class="reader">

        <header class="lesson-head">
          <div class="course-code-line">Basic Term · I · ABC&nbsp;101</div>
          <h1><em>ABC Notation</em><strong>One hundred and one.</strong></h1>
          <p class="kicker">A lightweight, human-readable language for writing music in plain text. We learn its anatomy from the headers down — and by the end you will read an <code>.abc</code> file the way a scribe reads a manuscript.</p>
          <div class="lesson-meta">
            <span><strong>Reading</strong> · 12 min</span>
            <span><strong>Exercise</strong> · 11 steps</span>
            <span><strong>Quiz</strong> · 15 questions</span>
            <span><strong>Lab</strong> · optional</span>
          </div>
        </header>

        <!-- INTRO -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="intro">
          <span class="section-num">§ I.</span>
          <h2>Introduction</h2>
          <p class="dropcap">ABC notation is a lightweight, human-readable format for representing music scores. It was developed in the early 1990s by Chris Walshaw, primarily for the use of folk and traditional music communities. The format is text-based, which makes it easy to share and distribute electronically &mdash; ABC files can be read on any device without specialised software.</p>
          <p>While ABC is excellent at representing simple melodies and tunes, it can become cumbersome for highly complex music with intricate rhythms and harmonies, and may not capture every nuance a MIDI file can. Despite being widely used there is no official standard, which leads to small variations in syntax and interpretation between programs.</p>

          <p class="pullquote">In short: <em>plain text, share-anywhere, read-anywhere.</em> The trade-off is that the realm of complexity belongs to MIDI.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- FEATURES -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="features">
          <span class="section-num">§ II.</span>
          <h2>Key features</h2>
          <dl class="deflist">
            <dt>TEXT-BASED</dt>
            <dd>ABC uses plain characters to represent musical elements, which makes writing and sharing easy.</dd>
            <dt>SIMPLE SYNTAX</dt>
            <dd>Each note is a letter (A&ndash;G) followed by optional modifiers: accidentals, octave indicators, and durations.</dd>
            <dt>HEADERS</dt>
            <dd>Files begin with header information that includes title, time signature, key, default note length, tempo and so on.</dd>
            <dt>NOTE REPRESENTATION</dt>
            <dd>Letters represent pitches; commas and apostrophes shift octaves; <code>^</code> marks a sharp, <code>_</code> a flat, <code>=</code> a natural.</dd>
            <dt>CHORDS &amp; TIES</dt>
            <dd>Chords sit inside square brackets, ties trail behind notes with a dash. Repeats and annotations are supported.</dd>
            <dt>DYNAMICS &amp; TEMPO</dt>
            <dd>Standard Italian terms enclosed in <code>+ +</code>; tempo set by the <code>Q:</code> field in the header.</dd>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <!-- HEADERS -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="headers">
          <span class="section-num">§ III.</span>
          <h2>Header syntax</h2>
          <p>Header information appears at the top of the file, one field per line, and provides the metadata for the tune. Below are the commonly used fields.</p>
          <table class="nice-table">
            <thead><tr><th style="width:8%;">Field</th><th style="width:30%;">Name</th><th>What it specifies</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td class="mono">X:</td><td>Index number</td><td>Optional. The tune's index when many sit in one file.</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">T:</td><td>Title</td><td>The title of the tune.</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">M:</td><td>Time signature</td><td>How many beats per measure, and which note gets the beat.</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">L:</td><td>Default note length</td><td>The duration of an unmodified note letter.</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">Q:</td><td>Tempo</td><td>Speed, in beats per minute.</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">K:</td><td>Key</td><td>The key signature (must be the last header line before the music).</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">C:</td><td>Composer</td><td>The composer of the tune.</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">P:</td><td>Parts</td><td>Number of parts or voices.</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">V:</td><td>Voice</td><td>The name of a particular voice or part.</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">%</td><td>Comment line</td><td>Anything after <code>%</code> is ignored by the player.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <p class="kicker">A complete header looks like this in practice:</p>
<pre>%abc-2.1
%%song-title       "No Matter What"
%%song-duration    2:52
%%song-transcriber Vydor

X: 11
T: No Matter What [Lute of Ages] (2:52)
%%part-name Lute of Ages
M: 4/4
Q: 116
L: 1/8
K: C maj</pre>
        </section>

        <!-- NOTE SYNTAX -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="notes">
          <span class="section-num">§ IV.</span>
          <h2>Note syntax</h2>
          <p>Each note is a letter from A to G corresponding to its pitch. Octaves are shifted by punctuation; accidentals by symbols; durations by numbers.</p>

          <h3>The full range</h3>

          <div class="staff-card" data-abc={`X:1
T:The Range
M:4/4
L:1/4
K:C
C, D, E, F, | G, A, B, C | D E F G | A B c d | e f g a | b c'4 |`}>
            <div class="staff-label"><span>From low C, to high c&prime; — every note named.</span><span class="lbl">Staff · I</span></div>
            <div class="staff-render"></div>
            <div class="staff-controls">
              <button class="play-btn">▶ Play</button>
              <span class="play-status"></span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <dl class="deflist">
            <dt>LOWER OCTAVE</dt>
            <dd>Trailing comma. <code>C,</code> is a low C.</dd>
            <dt>HIGHER OCTAVE</dt>
            <dd>Lowercase letter. <code>c</code> is a high C; <code>c&prime;</code> is the highest C with the apostrophe.</dd>
            <dt>SHARP</dt>
            <dd><code>^</code> before the letter. <code>^c</code> is C sharp.</dd>
            <dt>FLAT</dt>
            <dd><code>_</code> before the letter. <code>_b</code> is B flat.</dd>
            <dt>NATURAL</dt>
            <dd><code>=</code> before the letter, or simply the bare letter.</dd>
            <dt>CHORDS</dt>
            <dd>Square brackets. <code>[CEG]</code> is a C-major triad; <code>[FAC]</code>, <code>[CEGc]</code>.</dd>
            <dt>TIES</dt>
            <dd>A dash after the leading note. <code>C-</code> ties C to whatever follows.</dd>
            <dt>RESTS</dt>
            <dd><code>z</code> for a rest of the default note length; <code>z2</code> doubles it.</dd>
            <dt>BAR LINE</dt>
            <dd><code>|</code> ends a measure.</dd>
            <dt>DURATIONS</dt>
            <dd>A trailing number multiplies the default length: <code>C2</code> is twice; <code>C/2</code> is half.</dd>
          </dl>

          <h3>A small example</h3>

          <div class="staff-card" data-abc={`X:1
T:A Small Example
M:4/4
L:1/4
K:C
C2 D2 | [CEG]2 G2 | A B c2 | G4 ||`}>
            <div class="staff-label"><span>Two whole notes, a chord and a tied finish.</span><span class="lbl">Staff · II</span></div>
            <div class="staff-render"></div>
            <div class="staff-controls">
              <button class="play-btn">▶ Play</button>
              <span class="play-status"></span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- DYNAMICS -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="dynamics">
          <span class="section-num">§ V.</span>
          <h2>Dynamics</h2>
          <p>Dynamics convey volume and intensity. In ABC they are written as standard Italian terms enclosed by <code>+</code> on either side. The dynamic affects every note that follows until another is given.</p>

          <table class="nice-table">
            <thead><tr><th style="width:18%;">Marking</th><th style="width:32%;">Italian</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td class="mono">+ppp+</td><td><em>triple piano</em></td><td>Very, very soft</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">+pp+</td><td><em>pianissimo</em></td><td>Very soft</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">+p+</td><td><em>piano</em></td><td>Soft</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">+mp+</td><td><em>mezzo piano</em></td><td>Moderately soft</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">+mf+</td><td><em>mezzo forte</em></td><td>Moderately loud</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">+f+</td><td><em>forte</em></td><td>Loud</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">+ff+</td><td><em>fortissimo</em></td><td>Very loud</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="mono">+fff+</td><td><em>triple forte</em></td><td>Very, very loud</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p class="muted italic">A note from the workbench: there is no discernible difference between <code>fff</code> and <code>ffff</code>, nor between <code>ppp</code> and <code>pppp</code>. Three is the practical limit.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- TIMING -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="timing">
          <span class="section-num">§ VI.</span>
          <h2>Understanding timing</h2>
          <p>Timing in ABC is set by two header fields working together: <code>L:</code> (the default note length) and <code>M:</code> (the time signature).</p>
          <dl class="deflist">
            <dt>L: 1/4</dt><dd>A bare letter is a quarter note.</dd>
            <dt>L: 1/8</dt><dd>A bare letter is an eighth note.</dd>
            <dt>M: 4/4</dt><dd>Four beats per measure; quarter note gets the beat.</dd>
            <dt>M: 2/4</dt><dd>Two beats per measure.</dd>
            <dt>L: not set</dt><dd>Defaults to <code>1/8</code>.</dd>
          </dl>

          <h3>Worked example</h3>

          <div class="staff-card" data-abc={`X:1
T:Simple Melody
M:4/4
L:1/4
K:C
"^mf"C/2 D/2 E F2 | G2- G/2 A2 | G4- G2 E2 | D2- D2 z4 |`}>
            <div class="staff-label"><span>The example from the textbook, set to staff.</span><span class="lbl">Staff · III</span></div>
            <div class="staff-render"></div>
            <div class="staff-controls">
              <button class="play-btn">▶ Play</button>
              <span class="play-status"></span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <ul style="font-family: var(--body); padding-left: 18px;">
            <li>4/4 time signature; <code>L:1/4</code> &mdash; bare letter is a quarter note.</li>
            <li><code>C/2</code> and <code>D/2</code> are eighth notes (half of a quarter).</li>
            <li><code>E</code> is a quarter note.</li>
            <li><code>F2</code> is a half note (two beats).</li>
            <li><code>G2-</code> ties to the next <code>G</code>.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- PLAYGROUND -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="playground">
          <span class="section-num">§ VII.</span>
          <h2>The playground</h2>
          <p>Edit the <code>.abc</code> below and watch the staff redraw. Press <em>Play</em> to hear it. This is the editor we lean on through the whole exercise.</p>

          <div class="editor-card">
            <div class="editor-toolbar">
              <span>scribe.abc</span>
              <div class="ed-actions">
                <button class="ed-btn" id="resetBtn">↺ Reset</button>
                <button class="ed-btn" id="exNoMatter">load: No Matter What</button>
                <button class="ed-btn" id="exTwinkle">load: Twinkle</button>
                <button class="ed-btn primary" id="playEditor">▶ Play</button>
              </div>
            </div>
            <textarea class="editor" id="editor" spellcheck="false">X:1
T:A Tune of Your Own
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:120
K:C
+mf+ C D E F | G2 G2 | A G F E | D4 |
+f+ [CEG] [DFA] [EGB] [FAc] | G4 ||</textarea>
            <div class="editor-output">
              <div class="out-label">
                <span>Rendered staff</span>
                <span id="editorStatus" class="muted italic"></span>
              </div>
              <div id="editorStaff"></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="muted italic">Tip: try changing the tempo (<code>Q:</code>), the key (<code>K:</code>), or the meter (<code>M:</code>) and see what happens to the staves and the playback.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- EXERCISE -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="exercise">
          <span class="section-num">§ VIII.</span>
          <h2>The exercise</h2>
          <p>Open the <em>No Matter What</em> example in the playground above, then check off each step as you go. Your progress is kept locally so you can return mid-task.</p>
          <ul class="checkbox-list" id="exerciseList">
            <li>Find the title of the song.</li>
            <li>Locate the dynamic the instrument is set to.</li>
            <li>Find a change of dynamic somewhere in the piece.</li>
            <li>Find a chord (look for square brackets).</li>
            <li>Play the song in the player above.</li>
            <li>Change the tempo from 116 to 140, observe, then change back.</li>
            <li>Change the meter from 4/4 to 2/4, observe, then change back.</li>
            <li>Comment out the <code>L:</code> line with <code>%</code>, observe, then restore it.</li>
            <li>Change the note length from 1/8 to 1/4, observe, then restore.</li>
            <li>Change the dynamic from <code>+f+</code> to <code>+pp+</code>, observe, then restore.</li>
            <li>Extra credit — identify the chords in the piece by the notes inside the brackets.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- QUIZ -->
        <section class="lesson-section" id="quiz">
          <span class="section-num">§ IX.</span>
          <h2>The quiz</h2>
          <div class="quiz-card">
            <h3>Fifteen short questions</h3>
            <p class="quiz-meta">Type your answer or simply think it through, then reveal the master's answer.</p>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION I.</span>
              <p class="q-text">What does ABC in the name stand for?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">ABC notation stands for "A Basic Convention" — a simple text-based system for representing music in a way that is easy to read and share electronically.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION II.</span>
              <p class="q-text">In ABC notation, what is represented by <code>^C</code>?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">A C sharp. The <code>^</code> raises the note by a semitone.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION III.</span>
              <p class="q-text">How do you tie two notes together in ABC?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">With a dash <code>-</code> after the leading note. <code>C-C</code> ties two C's together.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION IV.</span>
              <p class="q-text">What does the <code>M:</code> field specify?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">The time signature of the tune.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION V.</span>
              <p class="q-text">What is the purpose of the <code>L:</code> field?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">It specifies the default note length — the duration of any note that does not carry its own length modifier.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION VI.</span>
              <p class="q-text">In a time signature <code>M:4/4</code>, how many beats are in each measure?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">Four beats per measure.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION VII.</span>
              <p class="q-text">What is the default note length if no <code>L:</code> field is given?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">An eighth note — <code>1/8</code>.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION VIII.</span>
              <p class="q-text">How would you represent a half note in ABC with a default note length of 1/4?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">As <code>C2</code> — twice the default length.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION IX.</span>
              <p class="q-text">Which symbol indicates the end of a measure?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">The bar line: <code>|</code>.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION X.</span>
              <p class="q-text">How do you represent a chord in ABC?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">Enclose the notes in square brackets — for example <code>[CEG]</code> for a C-major triad.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION XI.</span>
              <p class="q-text">Which header field specifies the title of the tune?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">The <code>T:</code> field.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION XII.</span>
              <p class="q-text">What is the function of the <code>X:</code> field?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">It specifies the index number of the tune — useful when many tunes share a single file.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION XIII.</span>
              <p class="q-text">How is a rest represented?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer">With <code>z</code>. <code>z</code> is a rest of the default note length; <code>z2</code> doubles it.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION XIV.</span>
              <p class="q-text">How would you represent the dynamic <em>fortissimo</em>?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer"><code>+ff+</code> — bracketed by plus signs.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quiz-q">
              <span class="q-num">QUESTION XV.</span>
              <p class="q-text">How would you represent a measure of four D quarter-notes with <code>L:1/4</code> and <code>M:4/4</code>?</p>
              <textarea placeholder="Your answer…"></textarea>
              <button class="reveal">Reveal answer →</button>
              <div class="answer"><code>D D D D |</code> — four bare D letters and a bar line.</div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- LESSON NAV -->
        <nav class="lesson-nav">
          <a href="/courses" class="prev">
            <span class="nav-label">← Catalogue</span>
            <span class="nav-title">Course of Study</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/courses#midi-101" class="next">
            <span class="nav-label">Next · II →</span>
            <span class="nav-title">MIDI 101</span>
          </a>
        </nav>

      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<script is:inline>
  // ---------- Render all data-abc staves ----------
  function renderAll() {
    document.querySelectorAll('.staff-card').forEach((card, i) => {
      const abc = card.getAttribute('data-abc');
      const target = card.querySelector('.staff-render');
      target.id = target.id || ('staff-' + i);
      try {
        const v = ABCJS.renderAbc(target, abc, {
          responsive: 'resize',
          staffwidth: 640,
          paddingtop: 4,
          paddingbottom: 4,
          paddingleft: 0,
          paddingright: 0,
          foregroundColor: '#1a140c',
        });
        card._visualObj = v[0];
      } catch (e) {
        target.innerHTML = '<div class="err" style="font-family:var(--mono);color:var(--oxblood);">Could not render: ' + e.message + '</div>';
      }
    });
  }

  // ---------- Audio playback for staff cards ----------
  async function playCard(card) {
    const visualObj = card._visualObj;
    const status = card.querySelector('.play-status');
    const btn = card.querySelector('.play-btn');
    if (!visualObj) { status.textContent = 'Nothing to play.'; return; }
    btn.disabled = true;
    status.textContent = 'tuning…';
    try {
      if (!ABCJS.synth.supportsAudio()) {
        status.textContent = 'Your browser does not support playback.';
        btn.disabled = false; return;
      }
      const synth = new ABCJS.synth.CreateSynth();
      await synth.init({ visualObj, options: { soundFontUrl: 'https://paulrosen.github.io/midi-js-soundfonts/abcjs/' } });
      await synth.prime();
      synth.start();
      status.textContent = '♪ playing…';
      const duration = (visualObj.getTotalTime ? visualObj.getTotalTime() : 4) * 1000;
      setTimeout(() => { btn.disabled = false; status.textContent = ''; }, duration + 400);
    } catch (e) {
      status.textContent = 'Playback failed.';
      btn.disabled = false;
    }
  }

  document.querySelectorAll('.staff-card .play-btn').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => playCard(btn.closest('.staff-card')));
  });

  // ---------- Live editor ----------
  const editor = document.getElementById('editor');
  const editorStaff = document.getElementById('editorStaff');
  const editorStatus = document.getElementById('editorStatus');
  const initial = editor.value;

  let editorVisual = null;
  function renderEditor() {
    try {
      const v = ABCJS.renderAbc(editorStaff, editor.value, {
        responsive: 'resize',
        staffwidth: 640,
        paddingtop: 6,
        paddingbottom: 6,
        paddingleft: 0,
        paddingright: 0,
      });
      editorVisual = v[0];
      editorStatus.textContent = 'rendered';
    } catch (e) {
      editorStaff.innerHTML = '<div class="err">Could not render: ' + e.message + '</div>';
      editorStatus.textContent = 'error';
    }
  }
  editor.addEventListener('input', () => {
    clearTimeout(editor._t);
    editor._t = setTimeout(renderEditor, 180);
  });

  document.getElementById('resetBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {
    editor.value = initial; renderEditor();
  });

  document.getElementById('exNoMatter').addEventListener('click', () => {
    editor.value = `X: 11
T: No Matter What [Lute of Ages]
M: 2/4
Q: 116
L: 1/8
K: C maj
+f+ [A,EA] z z [A,-E-A-] [A,EA] [EA] E/^F/A |
[A,EA] z z [A,-E-A-] [A,EA] [EA] E/^F/A |
[B,^FBd] z z [B,-F-B-d-] [B,FBd] [FB] [E/A/] [F/B/] [Bd] |
[D3A3d3^f3] [E,B,EG] [E,B,E] [E,2B,2E2] |`;
    renderEditor();
  });

  document.getElementById('exTwinkle').addEventListener('click', () => {
    editor.value = `X:1
T:Twinkle, Twinkle
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:100
K:C
+mf+ C C G G | A A G2 | F F E E | D D C2 |
G G F F | E E D2 | G G F F | E E D2 |
C C G G | A A G2 | F F E E | D D C2 ||`;
    renderEditor();
  });

  document.getElementById('playEditor').addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const btn = document.getElementById('playEditor');
    btn.disabled = true;
    editorStatus.textContent = 'tuning…';
    try {
      if (!editorVisual) renderEditor();
      if (!ABCJS.synth.supportsAudio()) { editorStatus.textContent = 'No audio support'; btn.disabled = false; return; }
      const synth = new ABCJS.synth.CreateSynth();
      await synth.init({ visualObj: editorVisual, options: { soundFontUrl: 'https://paulrosen.github.io/midi-js-soundfonts/abcjs/' } });
      await synth.prime();
      synth.start();
      editorStatus.textContent = '♪ playing…';
      const duration = (editorVisual.getTotalTime ? editorVisual.getTotalTime() : 4) * 1000;
      setTimeout(() => { btn.disabled = false; editorStatus.textContent = 'rendered'; }, duration + 400);
    } catch (e) {
      editorStatus.textContent = 'Playback failed';
      btn.disabled = false;
    }
  });

  // ---------- Exercise checkboxes (persist) ----------
  const ex = document.getElementById('exerciseList');
  const STORAGE = 'oldtoby-abc101-exercise';
  const saved = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(STORAGE) || '[]');
  [...ex.children].forEach((li, i) => {
    if (saved.includes(i)) li.classList.add('done');
    li.addEventListener('click', () => {
      li.classList.toggle('done');
      const done = [...ex.children].map((x, j) => x.classList.contains('done') ? j : -1).filter(j => j >= 0);
      localStorage.setItem(STORAGE, JSON.stringify(done));
    });
  });

  // ---------- Quiz reveal ----------
  document.querySelectorAll('.quiz-q .reveal').forEach(b => {
    b.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const q = b.closest('.quiz-q');
      q.classList.toggle('revealed');
      b.textContent = q.classList.contains('revealed') ? 'Hide answer ↑' : 'Reveal answer →';
    });
  });

  // ---------- Progress bar & TOC active state ----------
  const progressFill = document.getElementById('progressFill');
  const tocLinks = [...document.querySelectorAll('.toc-list a')];
  const sections = tocLinks.map(a => document.querySelector(a.getAttribute('href')));

  function onScroll() {
    const docH = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
    const pct = Math.min(100, Math.max(0, (window.scrollY / docH) * 100));
    progressFill.style.width = pct + '%';

    // Active TOC
    let active = 0;
    const y = window.scrollY + 120;
    sections.forEach((s, i) => { if (s && s.offsetTop <= y) active = i; });
    tocLinks.forEach((a, i) => a.classList.toggle('active', i === active));
  }
  window.addEventListener('scroll', onScroll, { passive: true });

  // ---------- Boot ----------
  window.addEventListener('load', () => {
    renderAll();
    renderEditor();
    onScroll();
  });
</script>

